profile.profileDescription: Use this profile if you want a system that is compliant with simple Darwin Core

label.name: Description
label.description: An account of the resource.

label.name: Source of description
label.description: Source of item description. This should be a formal citation if possible. For informal sources a narrative description is acceptable.

label.name: Caption
label.description: Short descriptive caption for item.

label.name: Georeference
label.description: Coordinates documenting the location of the item

label.name: Notes (internal use only)
label.description: Notes regarding item

label.name: dcterms:type
label.description: The nature or genre of the resource. For Darwin Core, recommended best practice is to use the name of the class that defines the root of the record.

label.name: dcterms:modified
label.description: The most recent date-time on which the resource was changed. For Darwin Core, recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: dcterms:language
label.description: A language of the resource. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC4646.

label.name: dcterms:rights
label.description: Information about rights held in and over the resource. Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.

label.name: dcterms:bibliographicCitation
label.description: A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used. Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.

label.name: institutionID
label.description: An identifier for the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label.name: collectionID
label.description: An identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived. For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use the identifier in a collections registry such as the Biodiversity Collections Index (http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/).

label.name: datasetID
label.description: An identifier for the set of data. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a collection or institution.

label.name: institutionCode
label.description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label.name: collectionCode
label.description: The name, acronym, coden, or initialism identifying the collection or data set from which the record was derived.

label.name: datasetName
label.description: The name identifying the data set from which the record was derived.

label.name: ownerInstitutionCode
label.description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having ownership of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label.name: basisOfRecord
label.description: The specific nature of the data record - a subtype of the dcterms:type. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Darwin Core Type Vocabulary (http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/type-vocabulary/index.htm).

label.name: informationWithheld
label.description: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.

label.name: dataGeneralizations
label.description: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.

label.name: dataGeneralizations
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of additional measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions about the record. Meant to provide a mechanism for structured content such as key-value pairs.

label.name: catalogNumber
label.description: An identifier (preferably unique) for the record within the data set or collection.

label.name: occurrenceDetails
label.description: A reference (publication, URI) to the most detailed information available about the Occurrence.

label.name: occurrenceRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Occurrence.

label.name: recordNumber
label.description: An identifier given to the Occurrence at the time it was recorded. Often serves as a link between field notes and an Occurrence record, such as a specimen collector's number.

label.name: individualID
label.description: An identifier for an individual or named group of individual organisms represented in the Occurrence. Meant to accommodate resampling of the same individual or group for monitoring purposes. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a data set.

label.name: individualCount
label.description: An identifier for an individual or named group of individual organisms represented in the Occurrence. Meant to accommodate resampling of the same individual or group for monitoring purposes. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a data set.

label.name: sex
label.description: The sex of the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: lifeStage
label.description: The age class or life stage of the biological individual(s) at the time the Occurrence was recorded. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: reproductiveCondition
label.description: The reproductive condition of the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: behavior
label.description: A description of the behavior shown by the subject at the time the Occurrence was recorded. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: establishmentMeans
label.description: The process by which the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence became established at the location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: occurrenceStatus
label.description: A statement about the presence or absence of a Taxon at a Location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: preparations
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of preparations and preservation methods for a specimen.

label.name: disposition
label.description: The current state of a specimen with respect to the collection identified in collectionCode or collectionID. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: otherCatalogNumbers
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of previous or alternate fully qualified catalog numbers or other human-used identifiers for the same Occurrence, whether in the current or any other data set or collection.

label.name: previousIdentifications
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of previous assignments of names to the Occurrence.

label.name: associatedSequences
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, global unique identifier, URI) of genetic sequence information associated with the Occurrence.

label.name: samplingProtocol
label.description: The name of, reference to, or description of the method or protocol used during an Event.

label.name: samplingEfforts
label.description: The amount of effort expended during an Event.

label.name: eventDate
label.description: The date-time or interval during which an Event occurred. For occurrences, this is the date-time when the event was recorded. Not suitable for a time in a geological context. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: eventTime
label.description: The time or interval during which an Event occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: startDayOfYear
label.description: The time or interval during which an Event occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: endDayOfYear
label.description: The latest ordinal day of the year on which the Event occurred (1 for January 1, 365 for December 31, except in a leap year, in which case it is 366).

label.name: year
label.description: The four-digit year in which the Event occurred, according to the Common Era Calendar.

label.name: month
label.description: The ordinal month in which the Event occurred.

label.name: day
label.description: The integer day of the month on which the Event occurred.

label.name: verbatimEventDate
label.description: The verbatim original representation of the date and time information for an Event.

label.name: habitat
label.description: A category or description of the habitat in which the Event occurred.

label.name: fieldNumber
label.description: An identifier given to the event in the field. Often serves as a link between field notes and the Event.

label.name: fieldNotes
label.description: One of a) an indicator of the existence of, b) a reference to (publication, URI), or c) the text of notes taken in the field about the Event.

label.name: eventRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Event.

label.name: locationID
label.description: An identifier for the set of location information (data associated with dcterms:Location). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

label.name: higherGeographyID
label.description: An identifier for the geographic region within which the Location occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an persistent identifier from a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label.name: higherGeography
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of geographic names less specific than the information captured in the locality term.

label.name: continent
label.description: The name of the continent in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names or the ISO 3166 Continent code.

label.name: waterBody
label.description: The name of the water body in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label.name: islandGroup
label.description: The name of the island group in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label.name: island
label.description: The name of the island on or near which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label.name: Country
label.description: The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. With its standard country code

label.name: stateProvince
label.description: The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which the Location occurs.

label.name: county
label.description: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than stateProvince (county, shire, department, etc.) in which the Location occurs.

label.name: municipality
label.description: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than county (city, municipality, etc.) in which the Location occurs. Do not use this term for a nearby named place that does not contain the actual location.

label.name: locality
label.description: The specific description of the place. Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography, continent, country, stateProvince, county, municipality, waterBody, island, islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.

label.name: verbatimLocality
label.description: The original textual description of the place.

label.name: verbatimElevation
label.description: The original description of the elevation (altitude, usually above sea level) of the Location.

label.name: minimumElevationInMeters
label.description: The lower limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

label.name: maximumElevationInMeters
label.description: The upper limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

label.name: verbatimDepth
label.description: The original description of the depth below the local surface.

label.name: minimumDepthInMeters
label.description: The lesser depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

label.name: maximumDepthInMeters
label.description: The greater depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

label.name: minimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters
label.description: The lesser distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

label.name: maximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters
label.description: The greater distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

label.name: locationAccordingTo
label.description: Information about the source of this Location information. Could be a publication (gazetteer), institution, or team of individuals.

label.name: locationRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Location.

label.name: pointRadiusSpatialFit
label.description: The ratio of the area of the point-radius (decimalLatitude, decimalLongitude, coordinateUncertaintyInMeters) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location.

label.name: footprintWKT
label.description: A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the shape (footprint, geometry) that defines the Location. A Location may have both a point-radius representation (see decimalLatitude) and a footprint representation, and they may differ from each other.

label.name: footprintSRS
label.description: A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the Spatial Reference System (SRS) for the footprintWKT of the Location. Do not use this term to describe the SRS of the decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude, even if it is the same as for the footprintWKT - use the geodeticDatum instead.

label.name: footprintSpatialFit
label.description: The ratio of the area of the footprint (footprintWKT) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location.

label.name: georeferencedBy
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the georeference (spatial representation) the Location.

label.name: georeferenceProtocol
label.description: A description or reference to the methods used to determine the spatial footprint, coordinates, and uncertainties.

label.name: georeferenceSources
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of maps, gazetteers, or other resources used to georeference the Location, described specifically enough to allow anyone in the future to use the same resources.

label.name: georeferenceVerificationStatus
label.description: A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: georeferenceRemarks
label.description: Notes or comments about the spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalized in the method referred to in georeferenceProtocol.

label.name: geologicalContextID
label.description: An identifier for the set of information associated with a GeologicalContext (the location within a geological context, such as stratigraphy). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

label.name: earliestEonOrLowestEonothem
label.description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic eon or lowest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name (Precambrian) attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: latestEonOrHighestEonothem
label.description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic eon or highest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name (Precambrian) attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: latestEonOrHighestEonothem
label.description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic era or lowest chronostratigraphic erathem attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: latestEraOrHighestErathem
label.description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic era or highest chronostratigraphic erathem attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: earliestPeriodOrLowestSystem
label.description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic period or lowest chronostratigraphic system attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: latestPeriodOrHighestSystem
label.description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic period or highest chronostratigraphic system attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: earliestEpochOrLowestSeries
label.description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic epoch or lowest chronostratigraphic series attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: latestEpochOrHighestSeries
label.description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic epoch or highest chronostratigraphic series attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: earliestAgeOrLowestStage
label.description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic age or lowest chronostratigraphic stage attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: latestAgeOrHighestStage
label.description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic age or highest chronostratigraphic stage attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: lowestBiostratigraphicZone
label.description: The full name of the lowest possible geological biostratigraphic zone of the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: highestBiostratigraphicZone
label.description: The full name of the highest possible geological biostratigraphic zone of the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: lithostratigraphicTerms
label.description: The combination of all litho-stratigraphic names for the rock from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: group
label.description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic group from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: formation
label.description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic formation from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: member
label.description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic member from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: bed
label.description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic bed from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: identificationID
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who assigned the Taxon to the subject.

label.name: dateIdentified
label.description: The date on which the subject was identified as representing the Taxon. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: identificationRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Identification.

label.name: identificationQualifier
label.description: A brief phrase or a standard term (cf., aff.) to express the determiner's doubts about the Identification.

label.name: typeStatus
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of nomenclatural types (type status, typified scientific name, publication) applied to the subject.

label.name: scientificName
label.description: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of an Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in the IdentificationQualifier term.

label.name: acceptedNameUsage
label.description: The full name, with authorship and date information if known, of the currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) taxon.

label.name: parentNameUsage
label.description: The full name, with authorship and date information if known, of the direct, most proximate higher-rank parent taxon (in a classification) of the most specific element of the scientificName.

label.name: originalNameUsage
label.description: The taxon name, with authorship and date information if known, as it originally appeared when first established under the rules of the associated nomenclaturalCode. The basionym (botany) or basonym (bacteriology) of the scientificName or the senior/earlier homonym for replaced names.

label.name: nameAccordingTo
label.description: The reference to the source in which the specific taxon concept circumscription is defined or implied - traditionally signified by the Latin sensu or sec. (from secundum, meaning according to). For taxa that result from identifications, a reference to the keys, monographs, experts and other sources should be given.

label.name: namePublishedIn
label.description: A reference for the publication in which the scientificName was originally established under the rules of the associated nomenclaturalCode.

label.name: specificEpithet
label.description: The name of the first or species epithet of the scientificName.

label.name: infraspecificEpithet
label.description: The name of the lowest or terminal infraspecific epithet of the scientificName, excluding any rank designation.

label.name: taxonRank
label.description: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in the scientificName. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: scientificNameAuthorship
label.description: The authorship information for the scientificName formatted according to the conventions of the applicable nomenclaturalCode.

label.name: vernacularName
label.description: A common or vernacular name.

label.name: nomenclaturalCode
label.description: The nomenclatural code (or codes in the case of an ambiregnal name) under which the scientificName is constructed. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: taxonomicStatus
label.description: The status of the use of the scientificName as a label for a taxon. Requires taxonomic opinion to define the scope of a taxon. Rules of priority then are used to define the taxonomic status of the nomenclature contained in that scope, combined with the experts opinion. It must be linked to a specific taxonomic reference that defines the concept. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: nomenclaturalStatus
label.description: The status related to the original publication of the name and its conformance to the relevant rules of nomenclature. It is based essentially on an algorithm according to the business rules of the code. It requires no taxonomic opinion.

label.name: taxonRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the taxon or name.

label.name: measurementID
label.description: An identifier for the MeasurementOrFact (information pertaining to measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

label.name: measurementType
label.description: The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: measurementValue
label.description: The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.

label.name: measurementAccuracy
label.description: The description of the potential error associated with the measurementValue.

label.name: measurementUnit
label.description: The units associated with the measurementValue. Recommended best practice is to use the International System of Units (SI).

label.name: measurementDeterminedDate
label.description: The date on which the MeasurementOrFact was made. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: measurementDeterminedBy
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the value of the MeasurementOrFact.

label.name: measurementMethod
label.description: A description of or reference to (publication, URI) the method or protocol used to determine the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.

label.name: measurementRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes accompanying the MeasurementOrFact.
